headline: Is Meta Stock A Buy? Facebook Parent Shares Rebound After Tariff Deal, Q1 Earnings
summary: Meta Platforms stock is attempting to rally back after a three month slump.  Shares of the Facebook parent company are ahead 17% in May, after slumping 5% in April, 14% in March and 3% in February.  Meta stock was hit by fears about tariffs and the removal of the "de minimis" import exemption slowing its advertising business.

headline: Nvidia’s earnings call must deliver on 3 things or else
summary: Nvidia will report its first-quarter results for fiscal year 2026 after the market closes on May 28. Despite slowing sales, analysts expect positive results for EPS and revenue. This earnings report is about more than just Nvidia; it’s a bellwether for the AI boom as a whole, which is showing signs of abatement. Yahoo Finance Executive Editor and host of the Opening Bid podcast, Brian Sozzi, breaks down the top three things investors should watch for during Nvidia's earnings call.

headline: Is Meta Platforms' Business in Trouble?
